title: The Fruit of the Tree
creator: Edith Wharton
description: LibriVox recording of The Fruit of the Tree, by Edith Wharton. Read by Margaret Espaillat. When published in 1907, this novel about the lives of a wealthy mill owner, her socially progressive husband and friends caused a stir due to its treatment of drug abuse, mercy killing, divorce and second marriages. (Summary by Margaret) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
